{% extends 'layout.html.twig' %}
{% set active = 'doc' %}

{% block content %}

    <h2>{{ 'Yaskef User Guide'|trans }}</h2>

    <h3>PHP snippets</h3>

    <p>In PHP mode, just type some PHP code in the code field, then click
    "Test" to see the result.
    </p>

    <p>You don't have to begin your code with the open_tag <code>&lt;?php</code><br/>
    If you need to put some html, don't forget to leave the PHP mode
    with <code>?&gt;</code>
    </p>

    <h3>Javascript snippets</h3>

    <p>As for version 1.0.0betaX, the javascript code is simply put inside
    a <code>&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;</code> tag.
    </p>

    <p>If you need to put some html, don't forget to leave the javascript tag
    with <code>&lt/script&gt;</code>
    </p>

    <h3>SQL snippets</h3>

    <p>Not very well tested, the SQL code is passed to the DBAL implementation
    choosen in prod.php.<br/>
    The default database is sqlite3. Other doctrine databases have not been
    tested yet.
    </p>

    <h3>Pastebin</h3>

    <p>
        If you have an account at <a href="http://pastebin.com/">pastebin.com</a>,
        and have created your user with the --pastebin option, you should have
        a "Paste to pastebin.com" button.
    </p>

    <p>
        You can choose the exposure and expiration you want for your paste
        by going to the profile page.
    </p>

    <h3>Profile</h3>

    <p>
        A part from the pastebin options, the profile page can be used
        to change your password...

